<doc id="911020" wikidata="Q2855663" url="?curid=911020" title="Merenre">
<text>Merenre () is an Ancient Egyptian name meaning &quot;(the one) whom Ra has loved&quot;. It has sometimes suggested that the Greek Μενθεσοῦφις (Menthesouphis) is a rendering of this name, but it may more likely be a metathesized rendering of the name . Merenre is the throne name of two pharaohs of the 6th Dynasty during the late Old Kingdom period:

*Pharaoh Merenre Nemtyemsaf I (2283–2278 BC),
*Pharaoh Merenre Nemtyemsaf II (2184–2183 BC), grandson of Merenre I

== See also ==
* Pyramid of Merenre, burial pyramid of pharaoh Merenre I.

